|----------------|\n| `src\\NX_MW\\libdl\\memwatch.c` | 2 (L457, L528) | 0 |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\memwatch.c` | 2 (L457, L528) | 0 |\n\n### Transformation\n\n**Windows ctime_s**: `errno_t ctime_s(char *buf, size_t sizeInBytes, const time_t *time)`\n\nBoth files are identical copies. For each occurrence:\n\n**Before** (L457):\n```c\nmwWrite( \"\\nStarted at %s\\n\", ctime( &tid ) );\n```\n\n**After**:\n```c\n{ char ctime_buf[26]; ctime_s(ctime_buf, sizeof(ctime_buf), &tid); mwWrite( \"\\nStarted at %s\\n\", ctime_buf ); }\n```\n\nOr using the function-top declaration style (preferred for this codebase):\nAdd `char ctime_buf[26];` to the local variable declarations of the enclosing function, then:\n```c\nctime_s(ctime_buf, sizeof(ctime_buf), &tid);\nmwWrite( \"\\nStarted at %s\\n\", ctime_buf );\n```\n\n### Special Cases\n- Lines 458 and 529 contain commented-out incorrect `ctime_s` attempts: `//mwWrite( \"\\nStarted at %s\\n\", ctime_s( NULL,0,&tid ) );`. The `ctime_s(` in these comments does NOT match the denylist pattern `\\bctime\\s*\\(` (because `ctime_s` is a different word). So these comments can remain unchanged. However, since the active line above them is being replaced, these commented-out lines become stale hints. Per the minimal-change principle, **leave them as-is** -- they do not trigger the denylist.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: localtime() -> localtime_s() [7 files, 12 occurrences, LOW-MEDIUM complexity]\n\n### Files -- Active Code\n| File | Occurrences | Notes |\n|------|------------|-------|\n| `src\\kcrt\\gosav\\gosavlib.c` | 1 (L1932) | Pointer derefs `date->` must change to `date_buf.` |\n| `src\\tool\\ErrorLog\\ErrorLogView.cpp` | 1 (L267) | C++ file, `pTm->` must change, `strftime` needs `&pTm_buf` |\n\n### Files -- Commented-Out Code Only (change function name in comments)\n| File | Occurrences | Notes |\n|------|------------|-------|\n| `src\\msg\\cotalk\\f_tlk.c` | 2 (L4529, L5074) | `//` comments |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\dfstat\\main.c` | 2 (L105, L