ernatives AND commented-out `//localtime()` calls. All three need attention:\n   - Active `gmtime()` -> replace with `gmtime_s()`\n   - Commented `//localtime()` -> change to `//localtime_s()` in the comment\n   - Commented `//gmtime_s()` -> already safe, no change\n\n3. **nxstat.c L672**: `tm_p=gmtime((const time_t *)&shdl_add_idx_p->tv.tv_sec)` followed by `tm_p->tm_mday`. The type cast stays; we just change the call and dereferences.\n\n4. **jotesttool.c** has the highest density (18 calls). All follow the same pattern. The variable `tim_t` (pointer) needs to become `tim_t_buf` (struct). All 18 `gmtime()` calls and their subsequent `tim_t->` accesses must be updated. There are also two more at L2097 and L2216.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: strerror() -> strerror_s() [9 files, 94 occurrences, MEDIUM complexity]\n\n### Files (all active code, all in NX_MW)\n| File | Active Calls | Commented Calls |\n|------|-------------|----------------|\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\uptrs.c` | 26 | 3 (L289, L954 area) |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\mctrs.c` | 16 | 0 |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\main.c` | 10 | 0 |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\libetc.c` | 6 | 0 |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\init.c` | 4 | 1 (L55) |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\deliv.c` | 2 | 0 |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\opsnexus\\alive.c` | 8 | 1 (L953) |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\libdl\\nexus_lib.c` | 8 | 0 |\n| `src\\NX_MW\\libdl\\library.c` | 9 | 0 |\n\n### Transformation\n\n**Windows strerror_s**: `errno_t strerror_s(char *buf, size_t sizeInBytes, int errnum)`\n\n**Universal pattern found in all files**:\n```c\n// BEFORE:\nsprintf(err_cp, \"malloc(): %s\", strerror(errno));\n\n// AFTER:\n{ char strerr_buf[256]; strerror_s(strerr_buf, sizeof(strerr_buf), errno); sprintf(err_cp, \"malloc(): %s\", strerr_buf); }\n```\n\nBetter, using function-level declaration:\nAdd `char strerr_buf[256];` at function top, then:\n```c\nstrerror_s(strerr_buf, sizeof(strerr_buf), errno);\nsprintf(err_cp, \"malloc(): %s\", strerr_buf);\n```\n\n### Key Design Decision: Variable